The paper deals with system identification using compressed sensing techniques, which is a common topic in the information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI) sub-categories. The use of sparse error correction and Toeplitz structured matrices also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper's focus on robustness and performance guarantees may also make it relevant to numerical analysis (cs.NA).
